main event: A single unidentified flying object was observed over Abilene, Texas for 1 hour on September 29, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as round, quarter-sized, and white with a light.
The object would stand still, then move rapidly in one direction before returning to its original position.
The object's color was different from the surrounding stars.
The object was capable of high-speed maneuvers, including appearing to fade but never fully disappearing.
Two civilian witnesses, a gas station attendant and a housewife, reported the sighting.
witnesses: a gas station attendant and a housewife
